channel.title: W3i.IQ5.fraud
channel.description: Well, I found this today on SpyBot... What is it exactly and where did I (or where could I) get it from? Just curious... I don't think removing will be too much of a problem...

item.title: W3i.IQ5.fraud
item.dc:creator: @Team_Rocket Team_Rocket
item.description:
@Team_Rocket wrote:

[quote=“tyb97, post:5, topic:462936”][quote=http://forums.spybot.info/showthread.php?t=64414]
W3i.IQ5.fraud is supposed to be the legit 7zip or other freeware installer. Instead it is a netinstaller which tries to fool the user via unusual graphical user interface to install adware. W3i is also trying to make it look like 7zip and other free software is their own product which is practically theft.
[/quote][/quote]

They also partner with Toolbars.
